                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; first words (headings or parts of
                           headings) of constituent texts; directives for the ministers; word ʾǝgäle
                           in supplication formulas; some interlineal musical signs; most of the
                           abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs and Ethiopic
                           numerals.&#xD; &#xD; The incipit parts of most of the constituent texts
                           are written alternately in red and black lines (e. g., fols. 1ra-rc,
                           49va-vc, 62ra-rc).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
