                              ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ወበቃለ፡ መምሕርነ፡ ኪዳነ፡
                              ማርያም።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#132rc">132rc</locus>: This is a book of šum ʾAgame
                              Kasa whose baptismal name is Walda ʾAragāwi, who has donated it to the
                              (church of) Madḫāne ʿĀlam ʾAddǝgrat so that it might be for him a
                              guide to the Kingdom of Heaven. He who stole it or erased (its text)
                              shall be excommunicated by the authority of Peter and Paul and by the
                              word of our mamhǝr Kidāna Māryām.</quote> he note is written in the
                           main hand. Šum ʾAgame Kasa (a son of rās<note> Sǝbḥāt) is also mentioned
                              in Additiones to Mss. AMM-008, AMQ-011, BGY-006, MKL-005, MKL-006. He
                              was governor of ʾAgame in 1914-18, 1941-48. Cp. HAGOS GEBRE YOHANNES,
                              “Political History of Tigray: Rivalry for power (1910-1935)”, PhD
                              thesis, Addis Abäba University, 2003, 46. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title of the work, ቅዳሤ፡, has been crudely inscribed
                           in green ink on the front cover.&#xD; - Tamallas-signs, in the shape of
                           two perpendicular lines, indicating the place where the omissions written
                           in the margins, in the main hand, belong: <locus target="#3vb"
